{
  "text": "The clinical information has been previously reported with detail in [CITATION_1] . In brief, EGM were obtained from 23 patients evaluated in EPS for arrhythmia ablation therapy at the Hospital General Universitario Gregorio Mara\u00f1\u00f3n in Madrid (Spain). Patients included in the study had previously implanted a Medtronic\u2122ICD, and a LV mapping procedure was performed for clinical reasons by using a 3D nonfluoroscopic Cardiac Navigation System (CNS). Patients (20 men and 3 women) were 69 \u00b1 10 (mean \u00b1 standard deviation) years old, and all of them had structural heart disease, namely, 18 post myocardial infraction, 3 idiopathic dilated cardiomyopathy, 1 bi-ventricular dysplasia, and 1 localized LV disynergy. All patients had documented previous VT, and the LV ejection fraction depression degree was estimated as mild (3), moderate (4), and severe (16 patients).",
